      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty is scoped out at MRL 2. The SST k-ω turbulence model is the community-accepted standard for internal rotating flows; the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is consistent with FDA guidance. Sensitivity of NIH to turbulence model choice documented in the sensitivity analysis (hasSensitivityAnalysis = true) and found to be < 12% across three candidate models."
